Your PerformanceProfile has been created successfully, but it has not been applied successfully.

The key part is:

Type: Degraded
Reason: TunedProfileDegraded

TuneD daemon issued one or more error message(s) during profile application.

This is not directly related to cpuPartitioningMode. It indicates the Node Tuning Operator (TuneD) failed to apply the profile.

First, check whether cpuPartitioningMode is enabled

Run:

oc get node ocp-sno.lab4.ocp.lan -o jsonpath='{.metadata.annotations.workload\.openshift\.io/enable-cpu-partitioning}{"\n"}'

If it returns:

true

then CPU partitioning is enabled.

If it returns:

false

or nothing, then CPU partitioning is not enabled.


---

Next, check the TuneD pod logs

Find the TuneD pod:

oc get pods -n openshift-cluster-node-tuning-operator

Then check its logs:

oc logs -n openshift-cluster-node-tuning-operator <tuned-pod-name> -c tuned

Look for errors such as:

CPU partitioning not enabled

Invalid CPU set

Hugepages configuration error

Real-time kernel error



---

Also check the generated MachineConfig

oc get mc

You should see a MachineConfig similar to:

50-performance-performance-master

Then verify the MachineConfigPool:

oc get mcp master
oc describe mcp master

See whether it is:

Updated=True

Updating=True

Degraded=True



---

Based on your profile

Your CPU allocation is valid:

Reserved: 0,28,56,84
Isolated: 1-27,29-55,57-83,85-111

This reserves one logical CPU from each NUMA group and isolates the rest, which is a supported layout.

The issue is most likely one of:

1. CPU partitioning is not enabled.


2. The required MachineConfig has not been applied yet (node reboot pending).


3. The real-time kernel or hugepages configuration failed.


4. TuneD encountered an application error.



Please run these commands and share the output:

oc get mcp master

oc get mc | grep performance

oc get pods -n openshift-cluster-node-tuning-operator

oc logs -n openshift-cluster-node-tuning-operator <tuned-pod-name> -c tuned

These outputs will pinpoint the exact reason why the PerformanceProfile is degraded.
